
UPDATE the PlasMapper's Vector Features Database 
-Written by savita, For more information contact Xioli or Ian

For adding sequence to the database

-Header of the Sequence should be like the example shown below.

example: ">ampicillin_resistance_gene2[SEL]{amp2},1015 bases, 5A8 checksum."

-[SEL] is a category. Chekcout for a proper category
-{} should contain a small string of the sequence decription, for example in above case
 is {amp2}.
-Sequence length is after {amp2}, Note that there should not be any space between {} and sequece
 length


Reindex the database after updation
-Command for indexing the database is

  formatdb -i <name of the file> -p F -o T
